        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 7.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Shall keep your priests' office for everything of the altar, and within the vail.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " That the Levites were made over to Aaron and his sons to relieve them of a great part of the mere routine and drudgery of their service was to be with them an additional and powerful motive for doing their priestly work so reverently and watchfully as to leave no excuse for sacrilegious intrusion. The altar (of burnt offering) and \"that within the vail (cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Hebrews 6:19",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") were the two points between which the exclusive duties of the priesthood lay, including the service of the holy place. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "A service of gift.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " A service which was not to be regarded as a burden, or a misfortune, or as a natural heritage and accident of birth, but to be received and cherished as a favour accorded to them by the goodness of God. Numbers 18:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
